From: vyos-ls1046a-build M0 implementation <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: 2026-05-26
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] dpaa: introduce pcd_ops / qmgmt_ops flavor abstraction

Introduce two ops tables (struct dpaa_pcd_ops, struct dpaa_qmgmt_ops) and a
flavor_priv void pointer in struct dpaa_priv. The two ops tables are
RCU-protected singletons registered by an optional flavor module via
dpaa_register_flavor_ops() / dpaa_unregister_flavor_ops(). When no flavor
module is loaded, both ops pointers are NULL and the core dpaa driver
exhibits zero behavioural change vs. mainline.

This is the in-tree replacement for the removed sdk_dpaa FM_PORT_SetPCD()
callback. Future flavor modules (FLAVOR=vpp AF_XDP zero-copy, FLAVOR=ask2
nft flowtable offload) implement these tables to install PCD trees, manage
XSK pools, etc. without touching dpaa_eth core code.

Spec reference: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 3 + sec 5.1 (M0).
No call sites are wired in this patch -- that lands in 0069.

Signed-off-by: vyos-ls1046a-build <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig
index 2b56066..14d3905 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig
@@ -9,3 +9,13 @@ menuconfig FSL_DPAA_ETH
 	  supporting the Freescale QorIQ chips.
 	  Depends on Freescale Buffer Manager and Queue Manager
 	  driver and Frame Manager Driver.
+
+config DPAA_FLAVOR_OPS
+	bool "DPAA: enable flavor ops abstraction (pcd_ops / qmgmt_ops)"
+	depends on FSL_DPAA_ETH
+	default y
+	help
+	  Compile in the dpaa_register_flavor_ops() / dpaa_unregister_flavor_ops()
+	  hooks so an out-of-tree or in-tree flavor module can attach PCD trees
+	  and XSK pool management to dpaa_eth without touching core code.
+	  Safe to leave on: with no flavor module loaded, behaviour is unchanged.
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Makefile b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Makefile
index 4f23e79..0926c74 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Makefile
@@ -10,4 +10,5 @@ ccflags-y += -I$(FMAN)
